cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network analysis and link prediction in real-world networks.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents algorithms for exact computation and randomized estimation of the proposed indices.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a novel distance measure and applies it to link prediction, which can be seen as a machine learning task.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper presents software implementations of the proposed algorithms.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with analyzing and predicting behavior in complex systems (networks).
